@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}

<style>
    body {
        background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0ea5e9 0%, #06b6d4 100%);
        min-height: 100vh;
    }

    .privacy-container {
        max-width: 900px;
        margin: 50px auto;
        background: white;
        border-radius: 20px;
        box-shadow: 0 20px 60px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.15);
        padding: 50px;
    }

    .privacy-header {
        text-align: center;
        margin-bottom: 40px;
        padding-bottom: 25px;
        border-bottom: 3px solid #0ea5e9;
    }

        .privacy-header h1 {
            color: #0f172a;
            font-size: 38px;
            font-weight: 700;
            margin-bottom: 12px;
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            justify-content: center;
            gap: 15px;
        }

        .privacy-header p {
            color: #64748b;
            font-size: 14px;
            font-weight: 500;
        }

    .privacy-section {
        margin-bottom: 35px;
    }

        .privacy-section h2 {
            color: #0ea5e9;
            font-size: 26px;
            font-weight: 600;
            margin-bottom: 18px;
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            gap: 12px;
        }

        .privacy-section h3 {
            color: #334155;
            font-size: 20px;
            font-weight: 600;
            margin-top: 20px;
            margin-bottom: 12px;
        }

        .privacy-section p {
            color: #475569;
            line-height: 1.9;
            margin-bottom: 16px;
            text-align: justify;
            font-size: 15px;
        }

        .privacy-section ul {
            margin-left: 30px;
            margin-bottom: 16px;
        }

        .privacy-section li {
            color: #475569;
            line-height: 1.9;
            margin-bottom: 10px;
            font-size: 15px;
        }

    .highlight-box {
        background: #f0f9ff;
        border-left: 5px solid #0ea5e9;
        padding: 25px;
        margin: 30px 0;
        border-radius: 8px;
    }

        .highlight-box h3 {
            color: #0369a1;
            margin-bottom: 12px;
            font-size: 20px;
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            gap: 10px;
        }

        .highlight-box p {
            color: #0369a1;
            margin: 0;
            font-weight: 500;
            line-height: 1.8;
        }

        .highlight-box ul {
            margin-top: 12px;
            margin-bottom: 0;
        }

        .highlight-box li {
            color: #0369a1;
        }

    .icon {
        font-size: 26px;
    }

    .contact-section {
        background: #f8fafc;
        border: 2px solid #e2e8f0;
        border-radius: 12px;
        padding: 30px;
        margin-top: 40px;
        text-align: center;
    }

        .contact-section h3 {
            color: #0f172a;
            font-size: 22px;
            margin-bottom: 15px;
        }

        .contact-section p {
            color: #64748b;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
        }

        .contact-section a {
            display: inline-block;
            background: #0ea5e9;
            color: white;
            padding: 12px 30px;
            border-radius: 8px;
            text-decoration: none;
            font-weight: 600;
            transition: background 0.3s ease;
        }

            .contact-section a:hover {
                background: #0284c7;
            }
</style>

<div class="privacy-container">
    <div class="privacy-header">
        <h1><span>📄</span> Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p>Last Updated: May 25, 2026</p>
    </div>

    <div class="privacy-section">
        <h2><span class="icon">📋</span> Introduction</h2>
        <p>
            Welcome to Offer Letter Generator. We understand the importance of protecting your confidential candidate information
            when creating offer letters. This Privacy Policy explains how our application handles document templates and candidate data
            during the offer letter generation process.
        </p>
        <p>
            Our application is designed as a document processing tool that helps HR teams generate professional, personalized offer letters
            by merging Word document templates with candidate information from Excel data files.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="privacy-section">
        <h2><span class="icon">🔒</span> Information We Process</h2>
        <p>When you use our offer letter generation service, we temporarily process the following information:</p>

        <h3>Document Templates</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Word document templates (.docx, .doc, .dotx, .dot) containing offer letter formats</li>
            <li>Templates with merge fields such as «CandidateName», «PositionTitle», «Salary», and other candidate-specific placeholders</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Candidate Data Files</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Excel files (.xlsx, .xls, .csv) containing candidate records</li>
            <li>Structured data including candidate names, positions, compensation, dates, and other employment details</li>
            <li>Multiple candidate records for batch processing</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Generated Offer Letters</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Merged Word documents or PDF files containing candidate-specific offer letters</li>
            <li>Single consolidated document or multiple individual letters (ZIP format)</li>
            <li>Optional digital signature images embedded in generated documents</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="privacy-section">
        <h2><span class="icon">⚙️</span> How We Process Your Data</h2>
        <p>
            Our application uses Syncfusion DocIO library to perform mail merge operations and document conversion.
            The processing workflow is as follows:
        </p>

        <h3>Document Processing Steps:</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Upload:</strong> Your Word template and Excel candidate data file are uploaded to the server's temporary memory</li>
            <li><strong>Mail Merge:</strong> Syncfusion DocIO performs mail merge operations to populate template fields with candidate data</li>
            <li><strong>Selection Processing:</strong> Process all candidates or generate a single offer letter by offer code</li>
            <li><strong>Format Detection:</strong> The system automatically detects the appropriate merge format based on your data structure</li>
            <li><strong>Signature Integration:</strong> If enabled, digital signature images are embedded at specified keyword locations</li>
            <li><strong>Format Conversion:</strong> The merged document is converted to your selected output format (DOCX or PDF)</li>
            <li><strong>Output Generation:</strong> Based on your selection, either a single document or batch ZIP file is created</li>
            <li><strong>Download:</strong> The generated file(s) are immediately sent to your browser for download</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="highlight-box">
        <h3><span>⚠️</span> Important Note</h3>
        <p>
            All processing happens locally in your browser, and files <strong>never</strong>
            go to any external server. Everything stays private and secure on your machine. ✔️
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="contact-section">
        <h3>📧 Questions or Concerns?</h3>
        <p>
            If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy or how we handle legal document processing with database integration,
            please contact support for technical assistance:
        </p>
        <a href="https://support.syncfusion.com/support/tickets/create" target="_blank">
            Contact Support
        </a>
    </div>
</div>